# EasyOrders custom themes — expanded reference

**Official docs:** [Custom Themes](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/category/custom-themes) · [Getting Started](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/getting-started) · [Palette](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/palette) · [Dynamic Theme Data](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/dynamic-theme-data) · [Liquid Reference](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/liquid-reference) · [Events](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/events-reference)

**Section docs:** [Layout](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/sections/layout-sections) · [Product](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/sections/product-sections) · [Home](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/sections/home-sections) · [Utility](https://themes-docs.easy-orders.net/docs/custom-themes/sections/utility-sections)

---

## 1) What a custom theme is

- A **full** custom theme means you own every section via **Liquid** + **CSS** + **JS** from scratch (not a CSS-only overlay on a fixed skeleton).
- The storefront renders each section with **LiquidJS** and injects store data (products, categories, merchant settings).
- **`style.css`** and **`script.js`** load on **every** page (often minified on upload).

